sec.p:
The functional specificity of Ras isoforms can also be attributed to the differential access to or affinity of the isoforms for activators and effectors. This specificity is cell-type and activating receptor-dependent in most cases. Yan et al. elucidated the comparative activation of effectors PI3K and Raf1 by Ras isoforms: PI3K was activated to a higher extent by H-Ras when compared to K-Ras, which activated Raf1 [154]. The affinity of GAP NF1 is four-fold higher for H-Ras when compared to N-Ras [155]. Different groups have published similar cell types and context-dependent isoform-specific preferential activation of an effector [21]. Functional specificity of Ras isoforms may arise from:
Different activation kinetics of Ras isoforms under the same receptor;
Spatiotemporal segregation of signaling complex, with activators and effectors having different space, time, and thresholds of activation;
Specific enrichment of substrates for activators or effectors in the microdomains containing specific Ras isoform.
